hopobject.body: How much is a First Class stamp? myogenix glutamine review To conduct the study, the team showed participants a series of circles, starting with one and leading up to eight. As they did so, the researchers used functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) to map participants' brains. They found that a clump of about 80,000 neurons, around the size of a postage stamp, lit up in the brains of all eight subjects.
